data.text:
If you are curious about where to watch and stream Camp Rock online, then your search ends right here. This family musical follows Mitchie Torres, who attends a summer music camp. She quickly starts lying about her background because everyone else is from rich and well-connected families. Torres ends up getting into endless trouble because of that. What will she do now? To find out, watch the movie available for streaming online.

Here’s where you can watch Camp Rock online.

Where can you watch and stream Camp Rock?

You can watch and stream Camp Rock on Disney Plus. This movie is directed by Matthew Diamond and is currently available for streaming on Disney Plus through a subscription.

The cast includes Demi Lovato as Mitchie Torres, Joe Jonas as Shane Gray, Meaghan Martin as Tess Tyler, Alyson Stoner as Caitlyn Gellar, Maria Canals-Barrera as Connie Torres, Daniel Fathers as Brown Cessario, Julie Brown as Dee La Duke, Anna Maria Perez de Tagle as Ella Pador, Jasmine Richards as Margaret Dupree, Jordan Francis as Barron James, Roshon Fegan as Sander Loyer, Nick Jonas as Nate Gray, Kevin Jonas as Jason Gray, Aaryn Doyle as Lola Scott, and more.

How to watch Camp Rock and stream online

You need to buy a Disney Plus subscription to watch and stream this movie online.

The most affordable Disney Plus ad-supported subscription plan costs $7.99 a month. You can also buy an ad-free subscription plan, which will cost $10.99 a month and $109.99 a year.

The official synopsis for Camp Rock reads:

“When Mitchie gets a chance to attend Camp Rock, her life takes an unpredictable twist, and she learns just how important it is to be true to yourself.”

For more Disney Plus updates, watch the first trailer of The Creator. Also, find out when The Haunted Mansion could start streaming on Disney Plus.
